[
    {
        "content": "<p>I've been playing around with the (excellent) grw tactic and had the following situation:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Preorder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">grw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- ⊢ b &lt; c</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>It would be ideal if <code>grw</code> made the goal <code>b ≤ c</code> instead. Is this doable? Simply marking <code>lt_of_le_of_lt'</code> as <code>@[gcongr]</code> doesn't work.</p>",
        "id": 535176135,
        "sender_full_name": "Albert Smith",
        "timestamp": 1755625087
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Since <code>grw</code> is a rewriting tactic, it just rewrites the left hand side into the right hand side, without modifying anything else in the expression. So unfortunately it doesn't modify the strictness of the inequality. (I agree it would be nice if it did this, but I don't have a clear idea of how to implement this)</p>\n<p>There will also be the <code>gconvert</code> tactic in the future which will work as follows:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Preorder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">gconvert</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- ⊢ b ≤ c</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>To get the behaviour of <code>gconvert h</code>, you can currently use <code>revert h; gcongr</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Preorder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">revert</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- ⊢ a &lt; b → a &lt; c</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">gcongr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- ⊢ b ≤ c</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This approach however only works when the shape of the hypothesis and the goal are the same. If the goal is something like <code>2 * a &lt; c</code>, then this doesn't work. In that case I would suggest using the <code>gcongr</code> tactic in combination with a <code>have</code> statement or a <code>calc</code> block:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">calc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">gcongr</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 535202191,
        "sender_full_name": "Jovan Gerbscheid",
        "timestamp": 1755636988
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, I see. I guess the most natural edit to <code>grw</code> would be to try relaxing the expected new goal's relation to ≤ whenever it's &lt;. But that could be 2x slower, and also doesn't work because it involves calling <code>gcongr</code> on a goal like <code>b ≤ c → a &lt; c</code>, which is not of the required form <code>f ⋯ ~ f ⋯</code>. A possible solution is to extend <code>gcongr</code> to support goals <code>f ⋯ ~ g ⋯</code> as long as f, g have the same signature (maybe this is only useful for this specific scenario)</p>",
        "id": 535230656,
        "sender_full_name": "Albert Smith",
        "timestamp": 1755658811
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>anyway, seems like it's not trivial; thanks for the alternatives</p>",
        "id": 535230821,
        "sender_full_name": "Albert Smith",
        "timestamp": 1755658943
    }
]